textBeforeTable: Call of Duty transports fans into a gripping, movie-like World War II combat experience where they must survive the chaos of battle as ordinary soldiers fighting together as a squad. Through 24 devastating game missions, players take on Nazi forces through epic assaults, featuring scores of soldiers and incredible special effects, played out through three Allied forces -- U.S., British and Russian, all fighting together toward one common goal -- to defeat the German-led Axis war machine. Call of Duty also delivers heart-thumping team-based, online multiplayer action for up to 32 soldiers. Worthplaying. The release has a lot on the extensive plans to market the game, but also has a bit on gameplay: Gamer's Hell and Call of Duty, Infinity Ward's World War II first-person shooter, is now available in stores in North America. In a related note, the Call of Duty "Intensity" Trailer can be found on Call of Duty Unleashes Massive Assault on Retail Shelves Nationwide is the press release announcing that Following through on the promise made a month ago (the game development equivalent of shooting the wings off a fly), [Oct 29, 2003, 11:41 am ET] - Share - Viewing Comments Ships Ahoy - Call of Duty
